plotfield.sh is a bash script prepared to make use of the MatrixPlot R function. It has been developed to allow an easy plotting of the WRF output fields contained in an ncdf file.

Although MatrixPlot.R allows the plotting of contour lines and arrows for vectorial fields, the bash script plotfield.sh does not support these features yet.

An example of how the bash script can be used is: 

q@wave:~$ bash plotfield.sh 'file=/Datos/FindMedicanes-V13/Rolf/Rolf-spnud-2011-11-05_00to2011-11-10_00/output/outputfile-slp.nc field=slp vlevel=3 timestep=40 xmin=-1 xmax=14 ymin=36 ymax=42 xticksint=4 yticksint=4 colorpalette=Spectral barlims=c(990,1010) barbreaks=seq(990,1010,by=5) barlabs=seq(990,1010,by=5) outname=slp-vlevel3-t40.pdf'

This example includes all the options supported so far. Only the flags 'file', 'field', 'timestep' and 'vlevel' -in case of 4D fields- are mandatory in the input arguments string. The others will take their default values if they are not specified. 
